contentrichtext.text: '''World Domination''' or '''Global Domination''' may refer to: * [[World Domination (Kompressor album)|''World Domination'' (Kompressor album)]], 2001 * [[World Domination (Naildown album)|''World Domination'' (Naildown album)]], 2005 * [[World Domination Enterprises]], a UK independent rock band * [[World Domination Recordings]], a US record label * [[Global Domination (video game)|''Global Domination'' (video game)]], a 1993 computer game * ''[[Global Conquest]]'', a 1992 computer game * [[World Domination (The Re-Visit)]], a continuation of The Pussycat Dolls tour - World Domination Tour == See also == * [[Superpower]], a state with a leading position in the international system and the ability to influence events and its own interests and project power on a worldwide scale to protect those interests * [[World government]], the notion of a single common political authority for all of humanity * [[Global governance]], the political interaction of transnational actors * [[List of largest empires]] by maximum extent of land area occupied * [[New World Order (conspiracy theory)]], theories whose theme is that a powerful and secretive elite of globalists are conspiring to eventually rule the world through an autonomous world government * [[Risk (game)|''Risk'' (game)]] or ''La ConquÃªte du Monde'', a strategy board game * ''[[Conquer the World]]'', a compilation of strategy games by Microprose * ''[[Family Guy: Stewie's Guide to World Domination]]'', a 2005 humor book about the TV show ''Family Guy'' written by producer Steve Callaghan * {{intitle}} * {{Lookfrom}} {{disambiguation}}
